description.excerpt:
The code can be used with any number of spatial dimensions, input channels (number of classes) and reference channels (the original code only allows 2D and RGB reference images); 
The GPU kernel uses the TensorFlow memory allocator, which is necessary because TensorFlow allocates most of the GPU memory by default and leaves almost none for CUDA (with large images/many channels it can become a problem); 
The weights of the CRF are more restricted in this version so that they do not encroach on the compatibility matrix's role; 
Support for batch_size >= 1; channel dimension is the last dimension (inputs are of the form (batch_size, ..., n_channels) with an arbitrary number of spatial dimensions in between).
